{
  "texts": [
    "As discussed in prior sections, DP sets a formal limit on any user's influence on the outcome of a computation.",
    "restrictions do not prevent leakage: Choquette-Choo et al. (2021) and Z.",
    "Li and Zhang (2021) show that attacks are possible in this threat model, by querying in the neighborhood of a target example.",
    "This is evidence that such obscurity claims should be justified as well with adaptive attacks.",
    "'Final step access' is where a model is produced with a chain of multiple algorithms, and an adversary can only access the output of the final step."
  ]
}